data.reddit:
(Sorry for formatting, on mobile)

Age:17 
Sex:M
Height:5’9
Weight:135
Race:Caucasian
Location: USA
Duration of complaint:6-7 months
Location on body: Lower/mid left abdomen
Medical conditions: One UTI 5 months in (probably not related, but decided to throw it in)
Medications: Doctors prescribed levsin, no result. Use enteric coated peppermint pills that have a limited effect.
Very limited drugs/smoking/alcohol

For the last several months I have been feeling a weird pressure in my abdomen. It seems like it’s probably my intestines. It’s a mix between very slight pain and discomfort.  It feel as if though something is pushing my belly slightly from the inside out. Usually happens when I’m on the train and I get very nervous and hot because there are usually no bathrooms nearby (not that I ever end up needing to use it, but I’m just scared that if I do need to there won’t be one). It also happens at home so I don’t think the train is the culprit. I have had no diarrhea or constipation either. I don’t look bloated and my stool looks normal. Sometimes it seems as if though I’m hyper focused on my stomach and then it starts to hurt. I can’t not think about it because it has been bothering me for so long that it’s become engrained in every day life. The thought that my stomach might hurt and the fact that I’m not sure what it is makes me anxious.

Usually during a test, playing video games, when I’m at work, sculpting/drawing, playing soccer I don’t feel any sort of discomfort or pain. 

I have went to the doctor and they said it was IBS and they prescribed levsin. Levsin did not help at all, and I never had any diarrhea or constipation or cramps so I don’t think it’s IBS. Also did a blood test and there was no sign of inflammation, bacterial infection, deficiencies, etc (everything was normal). 

The same doctor said it might be an anxiety disorder, but I have had no issues with anxiety prior to this issue.

I went to a gastroenterologist when symptoms first popped up and he said that it was probably something I had ate. It’s now been quite a long time and I’m sure it’s not anything I have eaten. I tried going gluten free and dairy free but I still had the same symptoms.

Guesses?

Thanks!
